                <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/> <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>V <expan><abbr>Q</abbr><ex cert="low"/></expan><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>ir</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>erfectissimus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>raeses</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>rovinciae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>R</abbr><ex>aetiae</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/>Secundinus <lb n="4"/><expan><abbr>praef</abbr><ex>ectus</ex></expan> legionis <lb n="5"/>eiusdem
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Altar, oberer Teil abgebrochen. In Z. 1 noch der untere Winkel eines V, dahinter noch der untere Bogen eines Q, auch O oder C/G möglich. Reste von roter Farbe in den Buchstaben. (B): AE 1901; CIL 03, 14370,12; Steinmetz: Z. 1 nicht gelesen.</p>
